ile Apps</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Service Content</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/10BIZ-TECHTIP-TOP/10BIZ-TECHTIP-TOP-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Apple</media:credit><media:description>In the Storage settings, Apple’s iOS software for iPad and iPhone shows how much of the device’s storage is being used and offers several ways to reclaim space.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Have You Bought a Tesla Recently? We Want to Hear From You.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/business/energy-environment/tesla-elon-musk-europe.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/business/energy-environment/tesla-elon-musk-europe.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/business/energy-environment/tesla-elon-musk-europe.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Tesla sales are rebounding in Europe even though many people have negative feelings about Elon Musk, the company’s chief executive. We want to know why.</description><dc:creator>Jack Ewing</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 04:00:24 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-reader-callout</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric Cars and Hybrids</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Service Content</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Earnings Reports</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tesla</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Europe</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/19/multimedia/19tesla-europe-callout-fkqv/19tesla-europe-callout-fkqv-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Nam Y. Huh/Associated Press</media:credit><media:description>Tesla’s car sales took a big hit in Europe last year, in part because many people were turned off by the political views of the company’s chief executive, Elon Musk.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Tesla Crash That Killed a Texas Woman Will be Investigated by Federal Regulators</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/22/business/tesla-texas-autopilot-crash-nhtsa.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/22/business/tesla-texas-autopilot-crash-nhtsa.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/22/business/tesla-texas-autopilot-crash-nhtsa.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The car’s driver-assistance system was in use when the crash killed a woman on Friday, the police said.</description><dc:creator>Lauren McCarthy</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2026 22:53:43 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Driverless Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Self-Driving Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric Cars and Hybrids</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Car Crash</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Automobile safety</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Fatalities</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">casualties</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tesla</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">National Highway Traffic Safety Administration</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Katy</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/22/multimedia/22biz-tesla-crash-1-cbhp/22biz-tesla-crash-1-cbhp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Mike Blake/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Tesla’s driver-assistance systems have been implicated in a number of accidents, some of them fatal.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>‘Hard Fork’ Live, Part 3: Differing Visions of an A.I. Future</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/podcasts/hard-fork-live-part-3-differing-visions-of-an-ai-future.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/podcasts/hard-fork-live-part-3-differing-visions-of-an-ai-future.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/19/podcasts/hard-fork-live-part-3-differing-visions-of-an-ai-future.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>One final episode from our live event, featuring a debate, questions from listeners and the dramatic and unplanned collapse of a dancing robot.</description><dc:creator>Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Rachel Cohn, Whitney Jones, Vjeran Pavic, Alyssa Moxley, Dan Powell, Elisheba Ittoop, Marion Lozano, Rowan Niemisto and Diane Wong</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 